This directory contains the PPPoE client data-plane and control-plane glue
used by the current PPPoE client / PPPoX feature work.

Provenance summary
- Parts of the original PPPoE client / PPPoX plugin layout were initially
  derived from the Apache-2.0-licensed RaydoNetworks implementation:
  https://github.com/raydonetworks/vpp-pppoeclient
- Where code lineage remains direct, the original RaydoNetworks copyright
  notices are preserved in the affected source headers.
- The imported PPP control-plane sources used by PPPoX are documented
  separately in ../pppox/pppd/README.import.

Current repository scope
- pppoeclient.c / node.c implement the PPPoE client discovery/session path
  used in this tree.
- pppox.c / node.c host the PPP control plane and bridge it to the imported
  pppd state machines.
- The current code has been substantially adapted for the modern VPP tree,
  including:
  - PPPoX virtual interface integration
  - current binary API / CLI / debug output paths
  - real-line interoperability fixes for duplicate discovery packets,
    reconnect timing, and control-plane state synchronization
  - DHCPv6 runtime observability / dependency split used by the Gerrit stack

Review expectations
- Treat the PPPoE client / PPPoX code as an evolved implementation with
  preserved open-source lineage, not as a verbatim drop of the original
  Raydo tree.
- When modifying the code, keep provenance and license headers intact and
  prefer small, well-explained changes over large structural rewrites.
